 },
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "04_—_Sce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# 04 — Scenario Builder\n\nThis notebook builds a full multi-piece trad pitch, sweeps the climber from the ground to the top, and identifies the worst-case fall position.\n\nReal-world scenario: a 30 m granite crack with four pieces of protection."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "import_r",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "import ropesim.notebook\nfrom ropesim import (\n    Rope, Scenario, AnchorSystem, AnchorType,\n    Bolt, BoltType, Cam, CamPlacement, RockType,\n    BelayDevice,\n)\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport numpy as np"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_1._Choo",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 1. Choose a rope"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "rope_=_R",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "rope = Rope.from_db('Sterling Evolution Dry 9.4')\nrope"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_2._Buil",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 2. Build protection anchors\n\nFour pieces at different heights simulating a typical trad pitch:\n- **8 m**: small cam in crack (CamPlacement.GOOD)\n- **14 m**: medium cam (CamPlacement.GOOD)\n- **20 m**: large cam in slightly wet crack (CamPlacement.MARGINAL)\n- **26 m**: two-bolt anchor (route top)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "def_cam_",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "def cam_anchor(mbs_kn: float, quality: CamPlacement) -> AnchorSystem:\n    c = Cam(mbs_kn=mbs_kn, placement_quality=quality, rock_type=RockType.GRANITE)\n    return AnchorSystem(components=[c], anchor_type=AnchorType.SINGLE_POINT)\n\ndef bolt_anchor(mbs_kn: float = 25.0) -> AnchorSystem:\n    b1 = Bolt(position=[0.0, 0.0], mbs_kn=mbs_kn,\n              bolt_type=BoltType.GLUE_IN, rock_type=RockType.GRANITE)\n    b2 = Bolt(position=[0.4, 0.0], mbs_kn=mbs_kn,\n              bolt_type=BoltType.GLUE_IN, rock_type=RockType.GRANITE)\n    return AnchorSystem(components=[b1, b2], anchor_type=AnchorType.QUAD)\n\nprotections = [\n    (8.0,  cam_anchor(10.0, CamPlacement.GOOD),     'Cam #1 (good)'),\n    (14.0, cam_anchor(10.0, CamPlacement.GOOD),     'Cam #2 (good)'),\n    (20.0, cam_anchor(8.0,  CamPlacement.MARGINAL), 'Cam #3 (marginal)'),\n    (26.0, bolt_anchor(25.0),                        'Bolt anchor (route top)'),\n]\n\nprint('Protection rack:')\nfor h, anchor, label in protections:\n    print(f'  {h:5.1f}m  {label}')"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_3._Buil",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 3. Build the Scenario"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "scenario",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "scenario = Scenario(\n    rope            = rope,\n    climber_mass_kg = 75.0,\n    belay_device    = BelayDevice.ATC_GUIDE,\n    belay_height_m  = 0.0,\n    temperature_c   = 12.0,  # cool granite in the shade\n)\n\nfor height, anchor, label in protections:\n    scenario.add_protection(height, anchor, label=label)\n\nprint(scenario)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_4._Simu",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 4. Simulate a specific fall\n\nClimber is 3 m above the last piece of gear (cam #3 at 20 m → climber at 23 m)."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "result_s",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "result_specific = scenario.simulate_fall(climber_height_m=23.0)\nresult_specific  # rich HTML card"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_5._Swee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 5. Sweep all positions from 5 m to 28 m\n\nThis is the key power feature: sweep 60 positions in a single call using the Rust parallel batch engine."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "sweep_=_",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "sweep = scenario.sweep_fall_positions(height_range=(5.0, 28.0), steps=60)\n\nprint(f'Worst-case position: {sweep.worst_height_m:.1f} m')\nprint(f'Worst-case peak:     {sweep.worst_peak_kn:.2f} kN')\nprint(f'Worst-case FF:       {sweep.fall_factors[sweep.worst_index]:.3f}')"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_6._Visu",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 6. Visualise the sweep"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "fig,_(ax",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(10, 6), sharex=True)\n\nheights     = sweep.climber_heights_m\npeak_forces = sweep.peak_forces_kn\nfall_factors = sweep.fall_factors\n\n# Colour bars by danger level\ncolours = ['#27ae60' if f <= 7.0 else '#f39c12' if f <= 10.0 else '#e74c3c'\n           for f in peak_forces]\n\nax1.bar(heights, peak_forces, width=0.35, color=colours, alpha=0.8)\nax1.axhline(9.0, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.9, label='EN 892 single limit')\nax1.set_ylabel('Peak force (kN)')\nax1.set_title('Scenario sweep: peak anchor force vs climber height')\nax1.legend(fontsize=8)\n\n# Mark protection points\nfor h, _, label in protections:\n    ax1.axvline(h, color='blue', linestyle=':', alpha=0.5)\n    ax1.text(h, ax1.get_ylim()[1]*0.92, label.split()[0], fontsize=7,\n             rotation=90, va='top', color='blue', alpha=0.7)\n\n# Mark worst\nwh = sweep.worst_height_m\nwf = sweep.worst_peak_kn\nax1.annotate(f'Worst: {wf:.1f}kN\\n@ {wh:.0f}m',\n             xy=(wh, wf), xytext=(wh+0.8, wf+0.3),\n             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='black'),\n             fontsize=8, color='black')\n\nax2.plot(heights, fall_factors, 'o-', color='#8e44ad', markersize=3, linewidth=1.5)\nax2.set_ylabel('Fall factor')\nax2.set_xlabel('Climber height (m)')\nax2.set_title('Fall factor vs climber height')\nfor h, _, _ in protections:\n    ax2.axvline(h, color='blue', linestyle=':', alpha=0.5)\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_7._Zipp",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 7. Zipper failure simulation\n\nStarting from the worst-case position, simulate a zipper: the highest piece fails, cascading load to the next."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "worst_h_",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "worst_h = sweep.worst_height_m\nzipper = scenario.simulate_zipper(climber_height_m=worst_h)\n\nprint(f'Zipper from {worst_h:.0f}m:')\nprint(f'  Pieces failed: {zipper.total_pieces_failed}')\nprint(f'  Ground fall:   {zipper.ground_fall_reached}')\nfor i, idx in enumerate(zipper.failure_sequence):\n    h_pro, _, label = protections[idx]\n    print(f'  Step {i+1}: {label} at {h_pro}m failed')"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_8._Per-",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## 8. Per-position risk table"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "print(f'",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "print(f'{\"Height\":>7}  {\"FF\":>6}  {\"Peak kN\":>8}  {\"Risk\"}')\nprint('-' * 38)\nfor h, ff, kn in zip(sweep.climber_heights_m, sweep.fall_factors, sweep.peak_forces_kn):\n    risk = ('HIGH   ' if kn > 10.0 else 'MEDIUM ' if kn > 7.0 else 'LOW    ')\n    flag = ' <-- WORST' if abs(h - sweep.worst_height_m) < 0.2 else ''\n    print(f'{h:7.1f}  {ff:6.3f}  {kn:8.2f}  {risk}{flag}')"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "_Key_tak",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Key takeaways\n\n- **Run-out sections** (climber high above last piece) drive the worst fall factors.\n- The first bolt or two on a pitch often produce the **highest fall factors** — protection close to the belay creates short rope-out with long fall distance.\n- A **marginal cam** at the key piece is the most dangerous failure scen